				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In other words, you can't use 16-bit writes, because then the top byte will go to $2105.  Writing $FF88 to $2104 as a 16-bit value would set all four BG layers to 16x16 tile size, set the BG3 priority bit, and put the PPU in Mode 7, and OAM would still be blank.<br /><br />More importantly, did you mean STY and not STA?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
							</td>
						</tr>
						</table>
					</td>
				</tr>
				</table>
			</td>
