						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">koitsu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">(i.e. same byte, written twice)</div><br /><br />Are you sure about this part? My understanding (based on higan) is that the A-bus address is always updated after every byte written regardless of transfer type.<br /><br />(Which, given that regular DMA size is measured in bytes and not &quot;transfer units&quot;, means that it <em>would</em> be equivalent to %000 for regular DMA, but not HDMA)</div>

