						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Revenant wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">the last demo I wrote/released uses %010 for CGRAM color gradients. Presumably, so does every other game that uses HDMA to perform color gradient effects.</div><br />I use %x11, so that I can set both the address and the colour with one channel.  This method wastes a write because the address gets hit twice, but unfortunately (p, p+1, p+1) is not an available HDMA pattern.<br /><br />Sadly, (p, p, p, p) isn't available either, so if you want to do &gt;8 consecutive colours you have to use regular DMA in an IRQ...</div>

